benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/catalog/simplePlan - Add a simple plan entry in the current version of the catalog

covered: Valid Payload Scenarios: TC01/TC02/TC07/TC12/TC13/TC19/TC20/TC21/TC23 demonstrate successful creation with valid payloads and catalog state variations.
Invalid Payload Scenarios: TC04/TC05/TC08/TC09/TC18 test missing fields, invalid values, empty/malformed body and input validation.
Duplicate Submission: TC06 validates conflict on an existing planId.
Large Payloads: TC15 exercises handling of very large payloads.
Authorization: TC10 covers HTTP 401 when authentication is missing or invalid.
Server Error Handling: TC11 (503 catalog unavailable) and TC14 (405 method not allowed) cover error responses for service unavailability and wrong method; TC16 also demonstrates retry scenario.
Concurrency and Integration: TC22 tests concurrent requests; TC23/TC24 cover integration and degraded integration scenarios.
Backward Compatibility: TC21 verifies compatibility with fields used by older API clients.
gaps: Rate Limiting: No tests for throttling or bursts.
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or caching validation.
Internal Server Error: No test simulates a 500 error from the database or service layer.
Additional Authorization coverage: Only one 401 scenario; no 403 or role-based checks.
Content-Type and Accept header edge cases: No tests for unsupported media type (415) or incorrect content-type handling.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting and throttling tests for POST /simplePlan.
Add tests validating caching headers for create responses (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache behavior.
Introduce tests that simulate server-side 500 errors and verify proper handling and retries.
Expand authorization scenarios to cover 403 Forbidden and role-based access controls.
Test for edge content-type scenarios (e.g., 415 Unsupported Media Type) and Accept header handling.
Consider negative performance tests or budgeted latency checks beyond 2 seconds threshold.
Assess idempotency by re-sending identical POST and observing deduplication behavior if applicable.
